    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 396.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-11-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 10, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 23d of October (No.
                            244) has been received. The President regrets that her Majesty’s
                            government has not more favorably considered our complaints against the
                            violations of municipal and international law, committed by British
                            subjects under the British flag, in the case of the <pb facs="0305" n="235" xml:id="pg_235"/> steamer “290,” or “Alabama.” It is to be
                            apprehended that attempts by the same and similar vessels to repeat the
                            same injuries will ultimately require a more deliberate consideration of
                            the subject than the government now seems willing to accord.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
